    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-15T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="659"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/1602: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Crane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-15T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>84. Chinese-Eastern Railway holds bill for transportation of Czechoslovak troops
                    leaving Siberia of more than three million gold dollars. Non-payment of this
                    amount seriously impairs railroad by weakening its economic position.</p>
                <p>Ascertain discreetly whether cost transportation Czechoslovak troops is direct
                    obligation of Czechoslovak Government or whether France immediately responsible
                    therefor.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
